<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Cash Flow<br />
</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A French bank is going to allow people to <a href="//bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/10/14/french-bank-to-allow-sending-money-with-tweets/">transfer money through Twitter</a>.</li>
<li>Here are a few lessons from a former gangster on how to <a href="//www.vice.com/read/the-firm-getting-caught-getting-away-and-getting-caught-again-345?">rob a bank</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Marketing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A Scottish travel agencyâs bookings <a href="//www.ttgdigital.com/news/thorne-travel-sees-110-rise-in-bookings-after-that-advert/4692991.article">rise 110 percent</a> after this spoof video goes viral.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Customer Service</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>That accounting firm employee who lost his job <a href="//m.bizjournals.com/philadelphia/morning_roundup/2014/10/fired-after-dust-up-with-comcast-customer-service.html">after complaining about Comcast&#8217;s service</a> will not be getting his job back.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the Country</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>AÂ  business owner inÂ Elkton, Md., is <a href="//www.cecildaily.com/business/article_4259ee30-01e3-5ebb-80ea-653508fae30c.html">recognized</a> as a âhometown hero.â</li>
<li>Some businesses in a small California town say <a href="https://www.turlockcitynews.com/life-social/item/3695-lander-businesses-say-homeless-encampment-driving-away-customers">they are losing</a> customers because of a nearby homeless encampment.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the World</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Finland is <a href="//fortune.com/2014/10/13/finland-blames-apple-for-economic-problems/">blaming Apple</a> for its economic problems.</li>
<li>Once a symbol of power, farming is now <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/10/13/world/asia/once-a-symbol-of-power-farming-now-an-economic-drag-in-china.html?p">an economic drag</a> in China.</li>
<li>United Kingdom shopping levels <a href="//www.theguardian.com/business/2014/oct/14/shopping-levels-fall-british-retail-consortium">fall to their lowest</a> point since 2008.</li>
<li>Amazon is expected to create <a href="//www.bbc.com/news/business-29594289">1,000 jobs</a> in Britain.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Social Media</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here&#8217;s how a 550-woman conference this past week <a href="//www.fastcompany.com/3037069/how-this-550-woman-conference-beat-super-bowl-ads-at-twitter?">did better on Twitter</a> than most Super Bowl ads do.</li>
